<DocsPage
  title="Installation"
  section="Getting Started"
  description="Install Primer and get up and running in under 5 minutes."
>
  <p>
    This guide walks you through installing Primer, starting the dashboard, connecting the Claude Code
    hook, and optionally enabling GitHub integration.
  </p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Python 3.12+</li>
    <li>Node.js 20+</li>
    <li>A running Claude Code installation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>1. Install the Server</h2>

  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/ccf/primer && cd primer
pip install -e ".[dev]"</code></pre>

  <p>Initialize the database and start the API:</p>

  <pre><code>alembic upgrade head
uvicorn primer.server.app:app --reload</code></pre>

  <p>The API is now running at <code>http://localhost:8000</code>. Verify with:</p>

  <pre><code>curl http://localhost:8000/health
# &#123;"status": "ok"&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Start the Dashboard</h2>

  <pre><code>cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev</code></pre>

  <p>
    Open <code>http://localhost:5173</code> in your browser. For development, expand the
    "Admin API Key" section and enter the default key: <code>primer-admin-dev-key</code>. This
    gives you full admin access to all views.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Seed Sample Data <span style="font-weight:400;font-size:0.85em;">(Optional)</span></h2>

  <p>To explore the dashboard with realistic data:</p>

  <pre><code>python scripts/seed_data.py</code></pre>

  <p>
    This creates 3 teams, 8 engineers with different usage personas, and ~90 days of session
    history with transcripts, tool usage, model usage, friction events, and git commits.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Install the SessionEnd Hook</h2>

  <p>The hook automatically uploads session data after each Claude Code session.</p>

  <p>First, create an engineer and get an API key:</p>

  <pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/engineers \
  -H "x-admin-key: primer-admin-dev-key" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '&#123;"name": "Your Name", "email": "you@example.com"&#125;'</code></pre>

  <p>Save the <code>api_key</code> from the response. Then install the hook:</p>

  <pre><code>export PRIMER_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:8000
export PRIMER_API_KEY=primer_...
python scripts/install_hook.py</code></pre>

  <p>
    This adds a <code>SessionEnd</code> entry to <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code>. After your
    next Claude Code session ends, the transcript is automatically uploaded to Primer.
  </p>

  <h3>Verify the Hook</h3>

  <p>After completing a Claude Code session, check that it appears:</p>

  <pre><code>curl http://localhost:8000/api/v1/sessions \
  -H "x-admin-key: primer-admin-dev-key" | python -m json.tool</code></pre>

  <h2>5. Register the MCP Server <span style="font-weight:400;font-size:0.85em;">(Optional)</span></h2>

  <p>The MCP sidecar lets Claude query your team's usage data during conversations.</p>

  <p>Add to <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code>:</p>

  <pre><code>&#123;
  "mcpServers": &#123;
    "primer": &#123;
      "command": "python",
      "args": ["-m", "primer.mcp.server"],
      "env": &#123;
        "PRIMER_SERVER_URL": "http://localhost:8000",
        "PRIMER_API_KEY": "primer_...",
        "PRIMER_ADMIN_API_KEY": "primer-admin-dev-key"
      &#125;
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <p>
    Claude will now have access to 5 tools: <code>sync</code>, <code>my_stats</code>,
    <code>team_overview</code>, <code>friction_report</code>, and <code>recommendations</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Next Steps</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Invite your team</strong> — Create engineers in the admin panel and distribute API keys</li>
    <li><strong>Configure alerts</strong> — Set friction spike and cost thresholds in Admin &gt; Alert Thresholds</li>
    <li><strong>Customize for production</strong> — Use Docker Compose and PostgreSQL for multi-user deployments</li>
    <li><strong>Connect GitHub</strong> — Link sessions to pull requests for AI contribution tracking</li>
  </ul>
</DocsPage>
